          Installation of Puppet for Debain:
          
1. Enable the Puppet Labs Package Repository for 12.04
    wget https://apt.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-precise.deb 
    sudo dpkg -i puppetlabs-release-precise.deb 
    sudo apt-get update
    
   2. Enable the Puppet Labs Package Repository for 14.04
    wget https://apt.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-trusty.deb
    sudo dpkg -i puppetlabs-release-trusty.deb 
    sudo apt-get update
    
Installation of Puppet for RedHat Linux on Standalone mode:

1. Enable the Puppet Labs Package Repository for Red Hat Linux 5:
	sudo rpm -ivh https://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-5.noarch.rpm
	
2. Enable the Puppet Labs Package Repository for Red Hat Linux 6:
	sudo rpm -ivh https://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-6.noarch.rpm

3. Enable the Puppet Labs Package Repository for Red Hat Linux 6:
	sudo rpm -ivh https://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-7.noarch.rpm

      Install puppet on Red Hat Linux 6:
1.  sudo rpm -ivh https://yum.puppetlabs.com/puppetlabs-release-el-6.noarch.rpm
2. Yum install puppet

Install Puppet on the Puppet Master Server Mode:
	sudo apt-get install puppetmaster
  
Install Puppet on Agent Nodes:
  sudo apt-get install puppet
